What is Terragrunt?
Terragrunt is a thin wrapper for Terraform that provides extra tools for keeping configurations DRY.

Installation:
brew install terragrunt

# Or download binary
wget https://github.com/gruntwork-io/terragrunt/releases/download/v0.50.0/terragrunt_linux_amd64
chmod +x terragrunt_linux_amd64
sudo mv terragrunt_linux_amd64 /usr/local/bin/terragrunt
Example Configuration:
terraform {
  source = "git::git@github.com:your-org/modules.git//ec2"
}

remote_state {
  backend = "s3"
  config = {
    bucket = "my-terraform-state"
    key    = "terraform.tfstate"
    region = "us-east-1"
  }
}

inputs = {
  instance_type = "t2.micro"
  environment   = "production"
}
